!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

friend /frɛnd/

(friends) 

1. N-COUNT A friend is someone who you know well and like, but who is not related to you. 朋友 

例： I had a long talk about this with my best friend. 我和我最好的朋友就此进行了长谈。 

例： She never was a close friend of mine. 她从来就不是我的密友。 

2. N-COUNT If one country refers to another as a friend , they mean that the other country is not an enemy of theirs. 盟国 

例： The president said that Japan is now a friend and international partner. 总统说日本现在是盟国和国际伙伴。 

3. N-PLURAL If you are friends with someone, you are their friend and they are yours. (与…是) 朋友 

例： I still wanted to be friends with Alison. 我仍然希望同艾莉森做朋友。 

例： We remained good friends. 我们一直是好朋友。 

4. N-PLURAL/N-IN-NAMES The friends of a country, cause, organization, or a famous politician are the people and organizations who help and support them. 支持者 

例： ...the friends of Israel. …以色列的支持者。 

5. PHRASE If you make friends with someone, you begin a friendship with them. You can also say that two people make friends . 同…交朋友 

例： He has made friends with the kids on the street. 他同街上的孩子们交上了朋友。 

例： Dennis made friends easily. 丹尼斯容易交上朋友。

